AllDialogue.VoiceLines["Persephone"] = {
	["0022"] = "What?! How dare...! Get out of here! Get out, or I shall make you!! Out with you!",
	["0023"] = "You died! You, you died...! Those burning feet, they... sputtered out, when you were born. But... now you're standing here before me. How...?",
	["0024"] = "Alive! Zagreus, he... even kept your name! You live, how can this be, you live? You live...! Oh, the cruel Fates! My son!",
	["0025"] = "Ah. He told you that, did he. That's good. That's good! Though, tell me something, Zagreus. How... is it that you found me? To have journeyed all this way, I scarce believe it.... Zagreus?",
	["0026"] = "No... no, that isn't it, it's that... you cannot stay here. You can't stay here.",
	["0027"] = "The Fates are cruel, Zagreus. You're bound to that place... same as your father. So they would have us say good-bye, for now. My heart soars, knowing you live. Then it breaks, that our time together was so brief.",
	["0028"] = "You tell him I demand it. And I demand he also tell me how come he, or for that matter Nyx, never sent notice that you lived! Olympus is all rife with schemers, but I was so naive to think that they were different.",
	["0029"] = "The Styx shall take you, then. Oh, Zagreus. Farewell, my son. Won't you come back to me? When you are able, please. Come back. I shall be waiting here. However long it takes.",
	["0043"] = "I wanted to see you, too. Come, speak quickly with me, that our time together here may be as full as possible, all right?",
	["0044"] = "I couldn't live with myself anymore, down there. After I left Olympus, a long story in itself, I came to be with your father, in the Underworld. It was a shock, to say the least. The others in your father's house were welcoming enough, but... I never felt that I belonged.",
	["0045"] = "No, no. Your father could be very difficult. Though, he was gentle, with me. Soon enough, we got on fine, better than fine, at times, but... when I was with child... why, I struggled terribly. Because... a child born of surface-dwellers could not live, down there.",
	["0046"] = "According to them, yes. According to your father, and to Nyx. Even having heard... I took my chances, anyway. But when you emerged stillborn... it was too much. I fled. I fled, and came to reside here. Above the notice of the Underworld. Beneath the notice of Olympus.",
	["0047"] = "I don't know. I'm wondering the same. But, oh, look at you, Zagreus! We're running out of time. It's happening again! Stay with me, please?",
	["0048"] = "Oh, my dear son! Then please... ask Hades what you asked of me! Why he would lie? Tell him I must know, the same as you. And you farewell. Until we meet again!",
	["0049"] = "Wait, slow down, Zagreus, what do you mean? He told me you would not survive your birth, yet here you are. How wasn't that a lie?",
	["0050"] = "He never expected you to survive? Then, forgive my asking, but... why did you? How did you? The Fates are not known for making mistakes when it comes to such things.",
	["0051"] = "Nyx... of course she was involved. I only managed to escape because of her. Then, she restored my stillborn son to life, and nurtured him? And, I never would have known, unless that child, fully grown and having learned the truth, defied his father, and then found me here?",
	["0052"] = "Would I have come back... to see my only child? Had I but known you lived... I would have gladly gone through hell again to see you, Zagreus. Of course I would have.",
	["0053"] = "What if he didn't want me coming back to him? Or seeing you? Oh no, you're fading again, Zagreus. You've pushed yourself too hard! But what is it you meant, by what you said?",
	["0055"] = "Yes. I knew them long enough to have decided yes, that they were trustworthy. As much as anyone I've ever met. But I also know never to be trusting to a fault. I have to consider the possibility I was deceived.",
	["0056"] = "Ah, hahaha! Well, they have a funny way of showing it, I think. Your father, so... you have to get through him each time you visit me?",
	["0057"] = "Protecting me? Why Zagreus, what do you mean by that? As you can see, I can fend for myself.",
	["0058"] = "What, how would you know something like that? Zagreus? Ah, curse the Fates, you're leaving me again...",
	["0060"] = "No... Zagreus, what have you done? You've led them here?",
	["0061"] = "But then... does Hades know of this? That Olympus is involved?",
	["0062"] = "So Nyx and Hades are against each other, then. And Olympus is helping you... but they don't know I'm here, as far as you're aware?",
	["0063"] = "That fool... what was he thinking? What is he thinking...? Do you suppose... he thinks that he's protecting me from them? Oh, no...",
	["0064"] = "Vindictiveness runs in the family, my son. Then, if Olympus is involved, that would explain a lot. I'm here, not there with them, as you can see. But, oh, it seems we'll have to speak some more, when next you return...",
	["0066"] = "That fool is trying to protect me even now. It wasn't he who absconded with me, my son. And it's more complicated even than that. I was content to leave. Willing to make my life within the Underworld. With your father.",
	["0067"] = "We have a tendency to be impetuous when we are younger, Zagreus. I'd heard all about your father before we met. Admired paintings of him. It was very awkward, at first. But he had a bluntness I fancied. A sense of principle. I much preferred him to his brothers, I can tell you that.",
	["0068"] = "...I think... there would be war between Olympus and your father, Zagreus, if they found out. Especially now. After all this. And after all this time. They slew their parents once. If the Titans could be wiped from this world, so can we all.",
	["0069"] = "I can see how your father, shrewd but also single-minded as he was, might have followed such a line of reasoning as that. Oh, Zagreus... what have I done?",
	["0071"] = "I am. Your father is no fool when it comes to matters such as this. Besides... all that has happened... it's my fault. I was selfish! And now both sides of our family threaten to be torn apart.",
	["0072"] = "Nyx may be veiling you from them as she veiled me when I fled here myself. But even her own powers aren't infallible. Each time you visit me, you are incurring risk. One small slip, and they shall find me. Discover your deception. Go home, Zagreus. Please.",
	["0073"] = "Oh, Zagreus... I cannot return. After all that happened between Hades and me, and everyone, I just cannot fathom the idea. Besides... the risks we're taking would be even greater if Olympus were to find me there, with him. And you.",
	["0074"] = "My son... I know you've made hard choices and sacrifices to be here with me. And I'm forever grateful to have finally met you. But this is my home, now, yes. While your home is below. Please, if not for your sake, then for mine... do not return. I love you, Zagreus. Good-bye.",
	["0076"] = "...You have your father's stubbornness. Listen to me. You're endangering everything you care about by coming here. Don't you understand? Besides...",
	["0077"] = "...The truth is that I like it here, Zagreus. I have done well for myself on my own. And your father, he has his domain to look after. The feelings he once had for me... feelings we shared... they fade, with time. You'll understand, someday.",
	["0078"] = "What do you mean he still loves me, Zagreus...? How would you know?",
	["0079"] = "You're fading, Son... you don't need to prove anything to me. Please don't do anything rash. All of us made our choices. Now we have to live with them. Isn't it enough, to know that I am safe? That I'm content to be alone?",
	["0080"] = "I... oh, my dear boy...",
	["0082"] = "I was fitted for those garments when I first arrived. They... were not my customary style. So Hades has a portrait of me, still. Why would he put it back on display, now?",
	["0083"] = "Because he... because he loves me still. Is that what you want me to say?",
	["0084"] = "All I really wanted was to leave Olympus. I didn't exactly abscond. I doubt I had much of a choice, but I went willingly. Perhaps Zeus knew how I felt, and thought he was doing me a favor. As for Hades... I grew to love him, yes. He always gave me my space.",
	["0085"] = "...I just don't know, my son. Olympus is behind me. And the Underworld... I cannot imagine I would be very welcome there after all this time.",
	["0086"] = "Oh, Zagreus, I almost missed you. Truthfully, I hoped that I could make it a surprise...",
	["0087"] = "My arrival. I'm going. To your home. To Cerberus. Nyx. Your father.",
	["0088"] = "I am. Now if you could just help me pack up my remaining things? Only a few loose odds I'm bringing, just in case. If we hurry, maybe you could join me, rather than return the customary way. Not something a mother ever wants to see.",
	["0089"] = "Just so happens I know somebody who can give us a ride.",
	["0090"] = "Doubtless he has pressing matters to attend to. So let's not keep him waiting any longer, Son. Come on, then!",
	["0091"] = "You're on the River Styx. No longer in the mortal realm, entirely.",
	["0092"] = "I know. My heart is racing. Nothing like a river journey to remind oneself that there's no turning back.",
	["0093"] = "We'll have plenty of time for them, I think! For now, best we keep quiet. Pretend we're just a couple of dead souls on their final voyage.",
	["0096?"] = "Mother, this family gathering you're planning... are all our relatives welcome? Because I was wondering if I could extend the invitation to a distant ancestor... you know... Chaos.",
	["0100"] = "That's quite all right; I do. In the name of Persephone, the Queen!! Open the gates!",
	["0116"] = "What can we do? We can make peace with them. And let them know the truth. So much of it as they would tolerate. Diplomacy is not your father's strong suit. But I am going to need you two to do exactly as I say. Do you understand?",
	["0117"] = "We're going to invite all of them to a little family gathering! Here. And you shall personally deliver them their invitations, Zagreus.",
	["0118"] = "They certainly shall not be fine with everything. But, Hades and I, we'll be prepared to tell them what they need to hear. Don't worry, I shall do the talking.",
	["0120"] = "Oh, you know! That we met, fell in love, eloped. Had a child. A child who, once grown, sought desperately to reconnect with his extended family. To the chagrin of his grim lord father...",
	["0121"] = "...Fortunately, our loving and dutiful son at last persuaded his mother and father to reveal their secretive relationship, and make an effort to rejoin their great family.",
	["0122"] = "I'll deal with her. Perhaps I'll have to visit her and the rest of them from time to time, if that's what it shall take. But I'll be back. I've no choice! Did you know that if you eat the seeds of an Underworld pomegranate, then you cannot leave for one month out of the year, per seed?",
	["0123"] = "Neither do they.",
	["0124"] = "Soon after you invite them all, I hope. Now, go. And trust in me, all right? We have a lot to learn of trust, I think.",
	["0126"] = "A bit of collaboration seemed in the spirit of things. We're a great, big family, Zagreus. Past time we started acting like one, no? Now, keep it up. And thank you for your help.",
	["0127"] = "Nyx's parent... you've been in contact, then? Look, if you feel it's the right thing to do, I trust your judgment. The spirit of this event is to bring the family together.",
	["0128"] = "Excellent, Zagreus! Congratulate him, Hades! On a job well done.",
	["0129"] = "It's known as trust, Hades. Or faith? They're similar. Try one, sometime! It'll be good for you. As for what we do next... why, we've a great, big feast we must prepare!",
	["0130"] = "Yes, good! Now then... we have a lot of work to go around, so why don't we call everyone on staff, and let them in on this, and dole out suitable responsibilities, all right?",
	["0131"] = "All right!",
	["0133"] = "Haha, well! I'm glad it worked out for the best. There's just one thing that happened that I ought to tell you about, Son. No secrets between us, and all. This... is quite difficult for me to say.",
	["0134"] = "Indeed... something like that. You're quite perceptive, have I ever told you, Zagreus? But yes, my mother, she was quite conflicted. Didn't know whether to smite me or to hold me, maybe both. And, yes. She asked that I come home... to my responsibilities.",
	["0135"] = "Oh, it's not as bad as that, it's just... if we are to keep the peace down here, then, I must spend some time up there. Every so often! But, I shall always return, in no time at all. I promised Hades, and I promise you.",
	["0136"] = "Soon, Zagreus. Perhaps by the time you're back.",
	["0138"] = "Tsk, you know the surface isn't good for you! Besides, you're needed here. But, if you really want to see it for yourself, someday, who knows? Perhaps eventually we'll figure out a way.",
	["0139?"] = "I have to say, Mother, that was a clever plan. Convincing Father to finally let somebody have some fun around here.",
	["0180"] = "Why, thank you, Thanatos! I'll take you up on that if I can think of anything anytime soon. But my, you've grown! I understand you've been looking after my son, in the meantime?",
	["0181?"] = "Queen Persephone. All of us, we are most pleased you're back. If there is anything that I can do to ease your acclimation to this House, you need but ask.",
	["0182"] = "Well, I can see that he has better taste than I do, Thanatos! I have a sense of how industrious you are. You just take care of yourself, please. And take care of each other, too, all right?",
	["0183"] = "Oh, please, Nyx! No formalities between us, right? It's wonderful to see you, too, my friend. The days there on the surface, they were very different, but the nights... I was reminded of our times together, here.",
	["0184"] = "Good times, most certainly! I try not to remember the others!",
	["0185"] = "Well, having built a little house all by myself up there, I think I'm up for anything! You know what it's like.",
	["0187"] = "Thank you, my friend. I have to tell you... it's good to be back.",
	["0188"] = "Oh, Cerberus! Doubtless you deserve the biggest thanks that this House still stands, don't you? Did you enjoy the treat I brought you from the surface?",
	["0189"] = "I thought you might. You wouldn't know it wasn't made of meat, I'll bet! I'll see if we can't grow you plenty more.",
	["0190"] = "You're such a good boy, aren't you, Cerberus? Yes you are! Guarded the place while I was out. And even let my son come visit me!",
	["0191"] = "Dusa! Wonderful to know you! This House is immaculate! Night-and-day difference from before. Now I know exactly whom to compliment.",
	["0192?"] = "Um, it's my great pleasure to make your acquaintance. Call me Dusa, please! I, I'm your House custodian? And I am at your service! Anything you need, just call, OK?",
	["0193"] = "I hoped, but did not know for certain till I heard from you just now, Overseer Megaera! And, if I may? I understand you have achieved an awful lot since I took my, erm, leave of absence from this House. I see why Nyx and Hades put their trust in you!",
	["0194"] = "Likewise, you be sure to let me know if my son there happens to make more trouble for you than you welcome in your life. All right?",
	["0195"] = "...Honored to have met you, great Achilles, our royal guard! Good to know whom to turn to, should anything run afoul around here. So it was you who instructed my son in the martial ways?",
	["0196"] = "I am proud! You know, you were already quite the name back on the surface when I lived upon Olympus. I should think your legend's spread much farther still, since then!",
	["0198?"] = "...Ah, but to think that our esteemed musician of the court is none other than you, Orpheus! In matters of music, at least, Hades and I have similar tastes. Anyway, I don't mean to keep you!",
	["0200"] = "It's true we have to look out for them indefinitely, while Olympus need only look out for them for a little while. But our relatives are always watching from their mountain! And if they do turn a blind eye once in a while... mortals aren't bad at fending for themselves.",
	["0201"] = "They like us, Hades! They praise us, tell one another about us. What do you expect? Would you rather they forgot about us?",
	["0202?"] = "...Oh, come on, Hades! Mortals are much more resilient than that! What, you think they'll show up at your gates here, all at once? They have our family looking out for them.",
	["0203"] = "Already taken care of. Though, the flooding in Asphodel, hm, that doesn't look like something we can clear up for quite some time. Fortunately, the residents seem to be getting accustomed to it.",
	["0204"] = "Well, they're probably contained up there, at least. And Zagreus has been keeping them in check, hasn't he?",
	["0205"] = "Oh, Hades... I think the shades around here have been through enough as it is! I don't mind them. After all the time I spent on my own, having some company has been a welcome change.",
	["0206"] = "Require? Look at this place, Hades. Look at me! I have everything! And so do you. Try not to worry quite so much. And be patient with your son. That's all I ask.",
	["0207"] = "I'm not going to tell you how to balance your work, your marriage, and your parental responsibilities. I don't think anybody on Olympus or below knows quite how best to manage that. So long as we do our best.",
	["0208"] = "The coast was nice enough, Hades. But nothing is ever perfect, right? No matter how hard you try. Still... I think we get quite close around here, every once in a while.",
	["0209"] = "The heart can make us do the strangest things, can't it?",
	["0222"] = "Oh, Zagreus, you're so thoughtful, truly! Your father never permitted Nectar out in the open so I'd practically forgotten its savor. Though, just a moment, I have something for you, too!",
	["0223"] = "For me? Are you quite sure? You know, this vintage must have made it all the way up from the surface, to the mountains, then to here. We've both had distant journeys, haven't we?",
	["0224"] = "I must confess I do enjoy having a good bottle of Nectar, every now and then. And you appear to have a careful eye for such bottles, from what I can tell!",
	["0225"] = "Thank you very much, my son! You know, gift-giving customs of the Underworld are just so much more straightforward than the complicated social graces of Olympus!",
	["0226"] = "Oh, this is wonderful, except... I'm wracked with guilt for having nothing much to give you, in return. You never even got a mother's love from me.",
	["0227"] = "I'd like that even more than this fine Nectar, Zagreus!",
	["0229"] = "Thank you, Zagreus. Let's hope you're right. I nurtured very many plants, at least, of that I can assure you! Perhaps my gardening experience provided a bit of a head start on this whole mothering thing.",
	["0230"] = "...Why, this really is Ambrosia! How did you even acquire this, Zagreus? It brings back memories, for certain. And, never the bad ones, which... I think it must be why we prize this stuff so much. This is for me?",
	["0231"] = "Oh, my son... I shall certainly not need Ambrosia to think back upon getting to know you with the greatest fondness. Thank you very much.",
	["0232"] = "You know, the last bottle you gave me brought more pleasant memories than I expected. No telling just how many more of them I've tucked away. Say, would it be all right if I shared this with your father?",
	["0233"] = "Haha, almost sounded like a no to me!",
	["0234"] = "Nonsense, there's also Cerberus! Present company excluded. Come on, Son. Your father has a lot of work to do, but I'm absolutely certain that he has fond memories of you. Though, I know that isn't reassuring, coming from me.",
	["0235"] = "This is splendid, Zagreus, but please! If there's one thing I've learned since we met, it's that the trust we share is at the very foundation of our relationships. Why shouldn't he know who this is from? Besides, I think he could figure it out.",
	["0236"] = "I'm sure enough! And if he isn't, I suppose it's more for me.",
	["0237"] = "...You know I always wanted to be a mother, Zagreus? But after you were born... I was certain I had lost my chance. Then one fine morning you just walked into my life. And here we are. I still cannot entirely believe it. What I mean is... I love you, Son. I'm doing my best.",
	["0238"] = "Ah, don't remind me. Imagine if I called you Zaggie-poo from when you were born to this very moment, that's how that name felt to me. I much preferred the name my father gave to me.",
	["0239"] = "He was kind to me. And funny! Little bringer of destruction, I was to him. I liked that. He was right, I was a terror. But then he passed. I was very little still. My mother never spoke of him again.",
	["0240"] = "I suppose I can see that. I thought I might end up like Father... growing old, wasting away. Then the time flew by, and I realized I was closer to Mother's side. Mortals certainly don't have it easy. But their limited days, it means... they live their lives to the fullest, I think.",
	["0244"] = "Ah, I was afraid of that. Well, don't despair. I placed a charm upon my seedlings there that ought to keep them flourishing well on their own. Your duty now is simply to escape. You keep it up!",
	["0245"] = "You know, I think it's gone all right so far! Thank you for asking, Son. Everyone has been quite welcoming. The darkness is a pleasant change of pace, and while this dress can be a little difficult to move in... I quite like it.",
	["0246"] = "I'm sure it can. And I do miss my little cottage here and there, but... I think I'm through running away. There may be times when it is necessary, of course. But no matter how far you run, it doesn't make your problems go away. You taught me that, you know.",
	["0248"] = "I understand. I think that when Hades told you he asked no forgiveness, he understood as well, and meant it. Well, for all his failings, I'm thankful that he did not teach you how to hate. For your own sake, if not for his.",
	["0250"] = "He says it's so you put forth your fullest effort every time. All this is a big adjustment for him as well. Not that it's any excuse for how he's treated you. Are you... all right, seeing us together?",
	["0251"] = "Things are good, Zagreus. I'm from Olympus... all the relationships I've ever known have been the complicated sort. But with your father... despite our different dispositions and interests... beneath it all, we share a simple understanding.",
	["0252"] = "That we're all we've got. And that we love each other. Through thick and thin.",
	["0253?"] = "Erm, so are things with you and Father... everything all right, so far?",
	["0254"] = "I was afraid of that... I wanted to believe the snow about my cottage, it was native to the climate there, but... seems that Mother took my absence harder than I thought. Oh, what have I done. All those poor people.",
	["0255?"] = "Mother, just how long has it been snowing on the surface, do you know? Because, it seems to me that Demeter... Grandmother, I should say, she... well, it's been very cold up there each time I've been.",
	["0256"] = "You know, it's funny... I think she was so overwhelmed to see me again that maybe something finally changed in her. I always thought she was utterly unyielding. She asked me if I truly came here by choice, and I put her at ease.",
	["0257"] = "I asked. She told me that she would. Warmth shall return to the surface. Some of the time, at least. Likely on a rigid schedule, knowing her. And perhaps not in the vicinity of our domain. She's not the sort to forgive and simply forget.",
	["0259"] = "Well, your father isn't always the conversationalist, and Nyx... she was the first chthonic god I ever met. I suppose she welcomed having another lady about the House.",
	["0261"] = "Thank you, my son. I know I wasn't there for most of the hard part, but... I'm here, now. Though, when I inevitably, inadvertently trample all over your feelings at some point, please tell me, all right?",
	["0266?"] = "How has it been for you so far, Mother? Reacclimating to all this. You said before it was a struggle. Must be very strange, being back. Being in darkness all the time.",
	["0269"] = "Not really, no. Nyx is very private when it comes to personal matters. But she has feelings and desires same as anybody. Well, mostly, but the point is... I know this meant a lot to her.",
	["0272"] = "Oh, I've no idea, probably not? But we were so moved by Orpheus' plea and song, that, well... I think your father took pity on him.",
	["0273"] = "I was. Your father knew I loved their music. Imagine my surprise to see him as our court musician, here!",
	["0274"] = "Oh, why... he gave me his calling card after he graciously helped get me out of here the first time. No doubt at Nyx's request, but still. Never thought I'd use it, but... I still kept it. Just in case.",
	["0276"] = "Well that was just a guess, now that you mention it. In any case, forgive me if I don't get swooped up in every household detail, all right?",
	["0277"] = "Not a lot of fruit trees take to this environment, my son. Though, there's something about pomegranates! Maybe it's that their seeds so resemble the gemstones your father likes so much. Or that they don't need much water.",
	["0278"] = "Well... I suppose there are a few. But I like pomegranates most of all.",
	["0279"] = "On the contrary, Zagreus! It has its own unique charm. As each garden does. I was impressed it wasn't left entirely to rot after my absence.",
	["0280"] = "He did, all right. Minus the part where you weren't allowed. Though, let's look after it from here, shall we?",
	["0281"] = "Oh, it's beautiful! I tried to persuade your father to hang it out in the hall but he's too coy about such things. Though, I like it where it is... a reminder to us, every day and night.",
	["0312?"] = "...And if you ever need anything at all, Your Royalness, you can always find me wide awake, right over there! Though I really shouldn't leave my post like this! Not even for you!",
	["0331"] = "Anybody would have lovingly raised my estranged son, while keeping safe my secret, eventually orchestrating an elaborate plot to reunite him with me, so that I might someday return, to have a Nectar with them in the lounge?",
	["0332"] = "...Whew! I'd say that went about as well as could have been expected! And the cleanup wasn't all that bad. For the most part.",
	["0333"] = "Zagreus... I may not be an expert... but here's what I've come to understand about how families work. At least our own. The thing is... how we speak to one another is even more important than the words we use. I think, deep down, everyone in our family knows this.",
	["0334"] = "The common ground in our family is that we want peace. Besides Ares, though even he would rather the conflict occur elsewhere. That elaborate tale... it's less a deception, and more a concession. A way of saying let's move on from the past, and start anew. No hard feelings.",
	["0335"] = "Well, let's see. My hard feelings are nothing next to the joy of having my son in my life. Your father never imagined his relationship with me could be out in the open. And my mother... she's just glad I'm alive.",
	["0336"] = "What can I tell you, Zagreus? We're family. You said it yourself to me before: We're stuck with one another. That any of us like each other in the slightest... it's a wonder and a blessing, I think.",
	["0337?"] = "It's done, Mother! Father. The invitations. Personally sent to everyone with whom I've been in contact. So, what do we do now?",
	["0018"] = "'Hades: I can no longer tolerate my life here in this place. So, I am leaving, even if it kills me. I won't be returning to Olympus. If there is a place where I belong in this world, it must be somewhere between heaven and hell. Perhaps it's on the coast and has a little garden. Take care of Cerberus; I shall miss him.'",
	["0019"] = "Who's there?",
	["0020"] = "Hello, indeed. Hold it right there.",
	["0030"] = "Zagreus!",
	["0031"] = "Zagreus...",
	["0032"] = "Zagreus?",
	["0033"] = "You're back!",
	["0034"] = "You're back...?",
	["0035"] = "Ah, you're back.",
	["0036"] = "My son!",
	["0037"] = "Is that you, Zagreus?",
	["0038"] = "Oh, it's you!",
	["0039"] = "Is that you?",
	["0040"] = "Zagreus, you're back!",
	["0041"] = "Welcome back, my son.",
	["0075"] = "Good-bye...!",
	["0094"] = "Charon, sir... have anything to listen to along the way?",
	["0095"] = "Oh, I like this one.",
	["0096"] = "Mm-hm!",
	["0097"] = "Mm-hm! Eurydice and Orpheus.",
	["0098"] = "Snow everywhere... Mother...",
	["0099"] = "We're here...!",
	["0102"] = "<Gasp> Cerberus...?",
	["0103"] = "Cerberus! I missed you so. And dutiful as ever, aren't you.",
	["0104"] = "Hades... you look tired. Though, I am not the only one you ought to be apologizing to.",
	["0105"] = "Oh, I've a thought or two about how we can settle that. Though I shall need for you and Zagreus to cooperate with me on a solution. Or, if you'd rather, I could just return the way I came?",
	["0106"] = "You're right, Hades! I can't. Certainly not by myself. So, are you going to help me, or what?",
	["0107"] = "Then, first, talk to your son.",
	["0109"] = "Oh, stop it, both of you. Don't make me regret this, Hades. Speak honestly with him. About yourself, not me. Go on.",
	["0111"] = "Perhaps you'll also tend to my little cottage while you're in the area? The garden doesn't take much care at all. I'd like to keep the place in decent shape. In case I cannot suffer this for long.",
	["0113"] = "Just do the best you can. And, clearly, I've work to do as well. We have a lot of it ahead of us, I'd say. So, shall we get started, then?",
	["0114"] = "Zagreus? Come here a moment, please.",
	["0139"] = "I'm going to miss you too, Son.",
	["0141"] = "It's not so bad, Son. I agree with that.",
	["0142"] = "Zagreus!",
	["0143"] = "Ah look who it is!",
	["0144"] = "Zagreus, I'm back!",
	["0145"] = "So good to see you, Son.",
	["0146"] = "Whew, I just got back!",
	["0147"] = "Good to be back at last.",
	["0181"] = "I know how mortals hate waiting around!",
	["0192"] = "Thank you, in turn!",
	["0198"] = "Oh, you're too kind!",
	["0284"] = "Good catch!",
	["0285"] = "Oh, good catch!",
	["0286"] = "Well caught.",
	["0202"] = "Well, we need them.",
	["0288"] = "Ooh look at that!",
	["0289"] = "Got that one all right!",
	["0290"] = "Alas for that.",
	["0291"] = "Next time, my son.",
	["0292"] = "Ah, well.",
	["0293"] = "Oof, almost!",
	["0294"] = "Can't win them all.",
	["0295"] = "Wasn't meant to be.",
	["0296"] = "Ah, there you are.",
	["0241"] = "Indeed, my son.",
	["0253"] = "Hahaha, no. You're plenty.",
	["0255"] = "We can, and shall.",
	["0266"] = "Indeed.",
	["0287"] = "Nicely done!",
	["0297"] = "Welcome, my son.",
	["0298"] = "Welcome back.",
	["0299"] = "Hello, my son.",
	["0300"] = "Zagreus.",
	["0301"] = "Greetings.",
	["0302"] = "Very well.",
	["0303"] = "Certainly.",
	["0304"] = "It shall be done!",
	["0305"] = "Yes, indeed.",
	["0306"] = "Sounds good to me.",
	["0307"] = "I'm grateful.",
	["0308"] = "Thank you very much.",
	["0309"] = "How very thoughtful.",
	["0310"] = "Oh, you're too kind.",
	["0311"] = "Why, thank you!",
	["0312"] = "I truly appreciate it.",
	["0313"] = "For you.",
	["0314"] = "This is for you.",
	["0315"] = "Ah, that's too bad.",
	["0316"] = "That's a bit unfortunate.",
	["0317"] = "Mm, I see...",
	["0318"] = "Well, what's to be done.",
	["0319"] = "Well done, Zagreus.",
	["0320"] = "Excellent work, my son.",
	["0321"] = "I knew you could do it.",
	["0322"] = "I can always count on you.",
	["0323"] = "Why, look at that!",
	["0324"] = "Oh, that's wonderful!",
	["0325"] = "Ah, I love it!",
	["0326"] = "Just what I always wanted!",
	["0327"] = "Hello, indeed!",
	["0328"] = "Zagreus... If you keep fighting out of here... it shall help keep appearances that everything is as it always was.",
	["0329"] = "Yes, indeed.",
	["0337"] = "Sounds good. I'll see you then.",
	["0162"] = "I'm sorry, Zagreus, I've pressing matters to attend to now.",
	["0163"] = "Do let me know if I can help with anything, all right?",
	["0164"] = "Your father's prouder of you than you think.",
	["0165"] = "Go make us proud, my son.",
	["0166"] = "Keeping the realm secure as ever, right?",
	["0167"] = "It's always nice to have a chat with you.",
	["0168"] = "I think the House is well enough in order as of late.",
	["0169"] = "I hope your last assignment turned out well.",
	["0170"] = "Do give yourself a break from time to time!",
	["0171"] = "I ever tell you you're the best son that a mother's ever had?",
	["0172"] = "Hope my little cottage on the coast is holding up!",
	["0173"] = "Please keep an eye on my garden on the surface when you get a chance.",
	["0174"] = "I'd say this garden's doing quite all right for now.",
	["0175"] = "Don't let your father get to you too much, all right?",
	["0176"] = "You're looking just as well as ever, Zagreus.",
	["0177"] = "You show your father who's in charge next chance you get, all right?",
	["0178"] = "The pomegranate trees are coming in nicely still, the tough old things.",
	["0179"] = "You'll let me know if there's something that I can do for you?",
	["0155"] = "We have to say farewell again, for now, my son. Olympus calls, but I'll be back, all right?",
	["0156"] = "I shall be leaving again for Olympus soon. I'll miss you, Son.",
	["0157"] = "I must go visit Mother on Olympus, Zagreus. I'll tell her you said hi.",
	["0158"] = "I have to go again, soon, Zagreus, all right? I'll see you soon.",
	["0159"] = "I'm due to visit Mount Olympus once again, so please be good to one another while I'm out.",
	["0160"] = "Time that I headed up to Mount Olympus, though you keep an eye on things till I get back?",
	["0161"] = "I have to go now, Zagreus, but I shall see you just as soon as I return.",
	["0148"] = "Things are well enough upon Olympus. Though, it's a relief to have come home again.",
	["0149"] = "Don't think I'll ever get fully accustomed to Olympus, Son.",
	["0150"] = "Zagreus, you're the most welcome sight I've seen in quite some time.",
	["0151"] = "Always such an exhausting journey, from Olympus down to here.",
	["0152"] = "I trust that you and Hades have been good to one another since I left?",
	["0153"] = "I'll tell you, it is so much colder up there on that mountaintop.",
	["0154"] = "This is a welcome sight from all the snow-capped mountaintops.",
	["0210"] = "Please excuse your father and me for the moment, Zagreus.",
	["0211"] = "Go on, Hades. Try saying something nice to him, for once.",
	["0216"] = "Don't go too hard on each other out there, all right?",
	["0217"] = "I've heard that you've been doing great out there lately, Zagreus.",
}
